'''Amalasuntha'''<ref>The name is also spelled '''Amalasuentha''', '''Amalaswintha''', '''Amalasuintha''', '''Amalswinthe''', '''Amalasontha''' and '''Amalsenta'''.</ref> ({{circa|495}}{{snd}}30 April 534/535) ruled the [[Ostrogoths]] as [[regent]] during the minority of her son from 526 to 534 and then as [[queen regnant]] from 534 to 535. She was the youngest daughter of [[Theoderic the Great]],<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|title=Amalasuntha|url=http://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/acref/9780195046526.001.0001/acref-9780195046526-e-0199|isbn=978-0-19-518792-2}}</ref>  and firmly believed in the upholding of Roman virtues and values. She is best known for her diplomatic relationship with [[Justinian I]], who invaded Italy in response to her assassination.<ref name=":3" />

